    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-12T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-12T12:00:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12515: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-12T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 12, 1918—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6244. Department’s number 6579, December 9th, 7 p.m. Mr. Pichon informs me that
                    while there is no doubt but that the Roumanian Government is in a frame of mind
                    to declare war on Germany, yet as a matter of fact the new Roumanian Government
                    will not go into power until the coming January. He understands that no
                    declaration of war could be made by the present Government as now constituted,
                    but he looks upon Roumania as to all intents and purposes an ally though not
                    formally so recognized.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
